      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " after ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (so Cyril, who, however, also reads it, consequently, a second time in the present passage, which Beza admits),[215] or have moved it up so as to follow ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (a few unimportant critical witnesses, approved by Rinck); some also have employed ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "exegetical",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " violence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", that is, was regarded either as a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "supplemental historical statement in order to prevent misunderstanding;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " so Erasmus, Castalio, Calvin, Vatablus, Calovius, Cornelius a Lapide, Jansen, and several others, including Lücke, Tholuck, Krabbe, De Wette, Maier, Baeumlein; or the emphasis was laid on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δεδεμένον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", to which word Grotius ascribed a force explanatory of the following denial, but Bengel one explanatory of the previous maltreatment. These exegetic attempts coincide in this, that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
